Merge pull request #361 from rlipman/roles-hyphen-bugfix

Escape the hyphens in the roles regexes

Escape the hyphens in the roles regexes

Inside square brackets, unescaped hyphens are position dependent. They
act like hyphens normally when at the beginning or end of a square
bracket expression. Otherwise it's used to signify a character range.

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/4068629/how-to-match-hyphens-with-regular-expression/4068725#4068725

Merge pull request #328 from sopel/patch-1

Updated to supported languages as of 20120801.

Updated to supported languages as of 20120801.

This updates the supportedlanguagesto the ones listed in the [Language reference](https://developers.google.com/translate/v2/using_rest#language-params) as of 20120801.

Specifically it adds:

*Azerbaijani (az)
*Basque (eu)
*Bengali (bn)
*Esperanto (eo
*Georgian (ka)
*Gujarati (gu)
*Haitian Creole (ht)
*Kannada (kn)
*Latin (la)
* Tamil (ta)
* Telugu (te)
* Urdu (ur)
